Taxonomic remarks. Leptoplanidae is a family composed by eight genera:
Leptoplana Ehrenberg, 1831
;
Hoploplana Laidlaw, 1902
;
Haploplana Bock, 1913
;
Notoplanides Palombi, 1928
;
Indiplana Strummer-Traunfels, 1933
;
Itannia Marcus, 1947
;
Longiprostatum Hyman, 1953
;
Parviplana Hyman, 1953
;
Leptoplanella Faubel, 1983
and Bivesiculoplana Pineda-López & González-Bulnes, 1984 . A new species of Leptoplanidae discovered in Oaxaca was not possible to determined in any of these genera.
